The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Festive beats

 Celebrating the arrival of the Bengali festive season, Happenings, Open Doors and EZCC present Drums amp; Rhythms, a special Durga Puja music event featuring percussionist Bikram Ghosh and his group, Rhythmscape. Equally popular among serious classical buffs and music aficionados of the young generation, Ghosh?s compositions are born of continued innovation and experiment. Creating path-breaking sounds, his music reflects influences wide in scope, ranging from Indian classical, Carnatic and western classical to jazz and folk. This evening, his creative energies find inspiration in Bengali tradition, as he tunes his rhythm to the pulsating beats of the dhak.

 Event: A music concert by Bikram Ghosh and his ensemble

 When: Tomorrow at 6 pm

 Where: Purbasree, IB 201 Salt Lake




